  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the best life advice?",
  "response": "The \"best\" life advice can vary greatly depending on individual circumstances, values, and goals. However, some universally applicable advice that resonates across cultures and contexts includes:\n\n1. **Be Kind and Compassionate**: Treat others with empathy and respect. Kindness enriches your life and the lives of those around you.\n\n2. **Stay Curious and Keep Learning**: Embrace a growth mindset. Every experience, whether positive or challenging, is an opportunity to learn and grow.\n\n3. **Take Care of Your Health**: Prioritize physical, mental, and emotional well-being. A healthy mind and body are the foundation for a fulfilling life.\n\n4. **Live Authentically**: Be true to yourself. Don\u2019t let societal expectations or others\u2019 opinions dictate your choices or define your happiness.\n\n5. **Cultivate Gratitude**: Focus on what you have rather than what you lack. Gratitude fosters contentment and resilience.\n\n6. **Embrace Change**: Life is full of uncertainty and impermanence. Adaptability and flexibility can help you navigate challenges and seize opportunities.\n\n7. **Forgive and Let Go**: Holding onto grudges or past mistakes only weighs you down. Forgiveness frees you to move forward.\n\n8. **Set Goals but Enjoy the Journey**: Strive for meaningful goals, but don\u2019t overlook the beauty and lessons in the present moment.\n\n9. **Build Meaningful Relationships**: Invest time in nurturing connections with family, friends, and community. Relationships are a cornerstone of happiness.\n\n10. **Take Responsibility for Your Choices**: Own your decisions and their consequences. This empowers you to shape your life intentionally.\n\n11. **Practice Self-Compassion**: Be as kind to yourself as you would be to a friend. Perfection is an illusion; embrace your imperfections.\n\n12. **Do What You Love**: Pursue passions and hobbies that bring you joy and fulfillment, even if they don\u2019t align with societal norms.\n\nUltimately, the \"best\" advice is what resonates with you personally and helps you live a life aligned with your values and purpose. Reflect on what truly matters to you, and let that guide your path.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
